@database "SetTaskPri"
@$VER: 1.1
@author "Daniel Westerberg - deniil@algonet.se"
@node main "SetTaskPri by Deniil 715!"

    @{fg shine}@{b}SetTaskPri v1.1 by Deniil 715!
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

  This little hack is for you who have a program which
  you think has wrong priority everytime it starts.

  Date: 2000-01-09

  @{" Usage    " link Usage} -> How do I use this thing?
  @{" Author   " link Author} -> Who made it?
  @{" OnyxSoft " link Onyxsoft} -> Where to get updates and other great programs!


@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

 @{fg shine}@{b}Usage
 ~~~~~@{ub}

  @{fg fill}General@{fg text}

    @{b}Taskname@{ub}
      This is the name of the task (or process) you want to
      change the priority of. It is case-sensitive.

    @{b}Priority@{ub}
      This is the priority it will be changed to.

    @{b}Check pri every@{ub}
      This is the delay between SetTaskPri will check if the
      priority has changed.

    @{b}Continously check the priority@{ub}
      This is if you want the priority continously check for
      changes. If it then will see a change in the priority
      of the task it will test to see if the task is still there.
      The priotity variable may change because the task is no
      longer available and the memory if freemem.

    @{b}Quit if task disappears@{ub}
      If "Continously check the priority" is selected and a
      change is notified but the task is no longer available,
      SetTaskPri will quit.

    @{b}DisplayBeep when a pri change is made@{ub}
      If you want a 'boing' or screenflash when the pri has
      been changed.

    @{b}Set now@{ub}
      With this button you can set the priority immediately.

    @{b}Test@{ub}
      This will tell you the current priority of the task.

    @{b}Hide@{ub}
      Iconifies the window.

    @{b}Quit@{ub}
      Exits the program.

  @{fg fill}Startup

    @{fg shine}What to do on startup@{fg text}

      @{b}Start hidden@{ub}
        This will just start the program iconified.

      @{b}Open window@{ub}
        This will start the program with the window open and do
        nothing more.

      @{b}Set priority and hide@{ub}
        This will start the program, set the priority of the
        task specified in the string and iconify.

      @{b}Wait 30 secs, then set pri and hide@{ub}
        This will start the program, wait for 30 seconds, then
        set the priority iconified.

      @{b}Set priority and open window@{ub}
        This will start the program with the window open and
        set the priority.

      @{b}Set priority and quit@{ub}
        This will simply set the priority and then quit.

      @{b}Wait 30 secs, set pri, then quit@{ub}
        This will start the program, wait for 30 secs, then
        set the priority and quit.

    @{b}Open window if setting the pri failed on startup@{ub}
      If for some reason the task was not found when starting,
      SetTaskPri wouldn't hide or quit but instead open it's
      window if this checkmark is set.


 You can also start it from CLI/Shell.

 @{u}CLI usage:@{uu}  SetTaskPri [pri] <task>

 The parameters will override the settings in the GUI.
 If only <task> is provided, the priority will be taken
 from the GUI-setting.


@endnode

